ğŸ”¹ Route Table 
A Route Table is a ğŸ‘‰ set of rules (routes) that the VPC router uses to forward traffic.
Destn ----- match ------ point to target 
eg: Packet leaves at subnet, checks for destination IP of packet find the matching route by checking destination 

Each route contains:
Destination â†’ CIDR block to match
Target â†’ Where traffic should go
Example:
Destination Target
x.x.x.0/16 local
default route Internet Gateway

When a packet leaves a subnet:
It checks the destination IP
The router performs longest prefix match
Traffic is forwarded to the matching target

ğŸ”¹ How It Works (Step-by-Step)
